{"title_page": "Future House Music", "text_new": "{{for|the genre|Future house}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n\n{{Infobox record label\n|image=Future House Music Logo.png\n|founded= July 2014\n|name=Future House Music\n|founder=Gino van Eijk<br>Aart van den Dool\n|location=[[Tilburg]], Netherlands\n|genre={{hlist|[[Future house]]|[[Tech House]]|[[Deep House]]|[[Bassline (music genre)|Bass House]]|[[Electro House]]|[[Brazilian Bass]]}}\n|website={{url|futurehousemusic.net}}\n}}\n\n'''Future House Music''' (abbreviated '''FHM''') is a Dutch record label and music network that specializes in the [[Future House]] genre. Their channel has over 1 million subscribers on YouTube.<ref name=\"TIOH\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.thisisourhouse.nl/features/future-house-music/ |title=Future House Music verovert de wereld: \u2018Publiek raakt klaar met EDM\u2019 |website=This Is Our House |language=nl-NL |access-date=26 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://weraveyou.com/2016/09/future-house-music-release-huge-playlist-spotify/ |title=Future House Music release a huge playlist on Spotify |date=13 September 2016 |website=We Rave You  |access-date=26 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nIt was started in 2014 by DJs, Gino van Eijk, Zak and Aart van den Dool. Originally starting out with genres such as [[electro house]], [[progressive house]], [[deep house]] and tech house, the label eventually focused on future house as, asserted by Van Eijk, it was \"placed on the map\" by the genre's pioneers [[Oliver Heldens]] and [[Tchami]]. Their YouTube channel was started after Van Eijk and Van Den Dool became inspired by Tchami's term-coining of future house.<ref name=\"TIOH\"/><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://universonline.nl/2017/05/11/jongensdroom-tilburgse-student-breekt-door-met-muzieklabel |title=Jongensdroom: Tilburgse student breekt door met muzieklabel |date=11 May 2017 |website=Univers  |access-date=26 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nThey eventually decided to use the channel as a platform to \"bundle\" music of the genre. They said \"We had the first mover advantage. Nobody had claimed the name 'Future House Music' yet. We did not know, of course, that it would be that big. But of course we also worked really hard for that.\" Since the formation of their YouTube channel, the identity of \"Future House Music\" included an addition of a record label (formed in 2016), merchandises and international events.<ref name=\"TIOH\"/><ref name=\"SKD\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.skiddle.com/news/all/Future-House-Music-heads-to-Leeds-/31277/ |title=Future House Music heads to Leeds |website=Skiddle.com  |access-date=26 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Artists==\n{{columns-list|colwidth=15em|style=width: 900px;|\n*Andy Bianchini<ref name=\"BP\"/>\n*Asketa\n*AWR<ref name=\"BP\"/>\n*Bobby Rock<ref name=\"BP\"/>\n*Bougenvilla<ref name=\"BP\"/>\n*[[Brooks (DJ)|Brooks]]<ref name=\"DJM\"/>\n*Dastic\n*DLMT<ref name=\"YEM\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.youredm.com/2016/10/26/dlmt-rawd-ft-stevyn-forbidden-dreams-future-house-music-free-dl/ |title=DLMT & RAWD ft. Stevyn \u2013 Forbidden Dreams [Future House Music] [Free DL] |date=26 October 2016 |website=Your EDM  |access-date=26 January 2018}}</ref>\n*[[D-Wayne]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwmusic/article/D-Wayne-Talks-to-Everybody-in-New-Track-Trippin-20171206 |title=D-Wayne Talks to Everybody in New Track 'Trippin' |last=Desk |first=BWW News  |access-date=26 January 2018}}</ref>\n*Ellis<ref name=\"BP\"/>\n*FaderX\n*Higher Self<ref name=\"BP\"/>\n*Holl & Rush<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.traxsource.com/title/861558/another-day/ |title=Holl & Rush, Jordan Jay \u2013 Another Day |date=11 September 2017  |website=traxsource  |access-date=10 February 2018}}</ref>\n*Jelle Slump<ref name=\"DJM\"/>\n*Jonas Aden<ref name=\"DJM\"/>\n*Junior J<ref name=\"BP\"/>\n*Lenx & Denx<ref name=\"BP\"/>\n*Maiki Vanics<ref name=\"BP\"/>\n*Matt Nash<ref name=\"BP\"/>\n*[[Merk & Kremont]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https